27/04/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Manouchehr Mottaki is asking for BiH's support in the UN over its nuclear ambitions. Mottaki, visiting Sarajevo on Monday (April 26th), said his country expects a "constructive and positive" approach from BiH as a non-permanent member of the UN Security Council, in case of a sanctions vote against Tehran. BiH Presidency Chairman Haris Silajdzic reiterated Sarajevo's support for the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) and its decisions regarding nuclear matters. He noted that BiH strives for membership in the EU and NATO and will consider these interests in voting at the UN. (Dnevni Avaz, Fena, Onasa, Dnevnik.ba, DPA, Reuters - 26/04/10)
